Create a JavaScript program that allows users to draw on an HTML5 canvas
model
Sure, here's a JavaScript program that allows users to draw on an HTML5 canvas:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Drawing on a Canvas</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <canvas id="myCanvas"></canvas>
    <script>
      const canvas = document.getElementById('myCanvas');
      const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');

      // Define the drawing function
      const draw = () => {
        ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(100, 100, 50, 0, 2 * Math.PI);
        ctx.stroke();
      };

      // Listen for user input
      addEventListener('mousemove', (e) => {
        const x = e.clientX;
        const y = e.clientY;

        // Draw the circle
        draw();

        // Update the circle's position
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(x, y, 5, 0, 2 * Math.PI);
        ctx.stroke();
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
```

This program defines a drawing function that clears the canvas, draws a circle at the mouse pointer's position, and updates the circle's position as the user moves the mouse.

Note: This program only allows the user to draw a single circle at a time, and it does not allow the user to draw other shapes or colors. To add more functionality, you can modify the program by adding more drawing functions or by adding event listeners for other user actions.

