write code for me image upload in php
model
Sure, here's a simple PHP code for image upload:
```php
<?php
if (!empty($_FILES["image"])) {
    $errors = [];
    $fileTmpName = $_FILES["image"]["tmp_name"];
    $fileName = $_FILES["image"]["name"];
    $fileSize = $_FILES["image"]["size"];
    $fileError = $_FILES["image"]["error"];
    $fileType = strtolower($_FILES["image"]["type"]);

    if ($fileSize > 2097152) {
        $errors[] = "File size is too big";
    }

    if ($fileError !== UPLOAD_ERR_OK) {
        $errors[] = "Upload error";
    }

    if (!in_array($fileType, ["jpg", "jpeg", "png", "gif"])) {
        $errors[] = "File type is not allowed";
    }

    if (empty($errors)) {
        $targetDir = "uploads";
        $targetFilePath = $targetDir . "/" . $fileName;
        $uploadFile = move_uploaded_file($fileTmpName, $targetFilePath);

        if ($uploadFile) {
            echo "Image uploaded successfully";
        } else {
            echo "Image upload failed";
        }
    } else {
        echo "Error: " . implode(", ", $errors);
    }
} else {
    echo "Please select an image to upload";
}
?>
```
This code will allow users to upload images to the `uploads` directory, but it will only allow images of the following file types: `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.png`, `.gif`. It will also check if the file size is too big or if there is an upload error. If there is an error, it will display an error message and not allow the user to upload the image.

